5:
Stella, wait for me! 
I heard you're going out to gather 
herbs. As your big brother, I'll tag 
along and protect you!
9:
Miles! I could hear you all the way 
from the World Flipper!
Sounds like you're still playing 
pretend...
13:
I'm supposed to be your frail little 
sister, right?
17:
Exactly! I'm glad you remembered. 
Knights unleash their true power to 
defend the defenseless!
20:
That means I need someone to 
protect if I wanna look the part!
24:
I see. There's more to being a knight 
than I thought.
28: H-he's not a REAL knight, Stella.
31:
Either way, I'm going to go collect 
those herbs. You are welcome to 
accompany me.
35:
Those two worry me...
But I suppose he'll only listen to Stella 
anyhow.
36: Keep an eye on him, Stella.
40:
Look! I found some!
There are a whole bunch!
44: Hmm? Whew, that's a strong scent.
47:
Why did you decide to become a 
knight, Miles? Does it have to do with 
your made-up sister?
51:
Oh, that's all from a play. It's about a 
knight who fights to rescue his frail, 
sickly sister. The lead is a big 
inspiration!
56:
His name's Geralt Dawnshield, and 
when he comes on stage there's a 
bright flash as he raises his shield like 
THIS.
64:
You don't have to be Kiara, but you DO 
have to be my little sister! Without a 
little sister to protect, I... I'd...
74:
That'll have to wait! Stella, stand back! 
I'll defend you!
82:
The shield... It cracked! 
Miles, we should flee.
86:
Never fear! I'll protect you! 
I swear it!
93:
Uh oh! It's winding up for a charge! 
What did we do to make it so mad?
96: All we've done is gather some—
110:
The herbs. I believe the scent drew the 
boar to us.
124:
You don't stand a chance against the 
two of us! Let's toss herbs everywhere 
and confuse it!
128:
That appears to have had the 
opposite effect.
135: But it won't get past me!
143:
I've still got plenty where that came 
from, fiend!
150:
Miles, the shield is barely holding itself 
together. 
We MUST flee!
168: Did he get in ANOTHER fight?
170:
Not Miles, it was the other kids—They 
ganged up on him, the poor thing. I'm 
going to go give that USELESS teacher 
a piece of my mind!
172:
I'll go too. I'll make sure they hold ALL 
of those brats responsible for this! 
They'll never touch another hair on his 
sweet head!
176:
Shh, don't worry, Miles. You'll always 
be Daddy's special boy. Let us grown 
ups handle the scary stuff, okay?
177:
Poor baby... You're our one and only 
sunshine. Everything's okay now.
179: Don't... Don't tell the teacher... No!
181:
Hmph! What do you think YOU'RE 
doing here? You told on us!
183:
Yeah! Now the teacher's mad! I don't 
want to play with a tattle-tale!
185:
Me either! You can't be our friend 
anymore! Tattle-tales don't deserve 
friends!
189:
Alone, alone, woe was I!
Alone I traversed the lonely tides,
Alone—Lo! But for yonder light!
191:
Kiara! My sister, starlight twinkling in 
her dewy eyes—
192:
The power I lost, by that light tethered!
My shield stronger than 'twere ever—
For the knowledge, we are together!
194:
A slash! A flash!
Kiara! My sister, plagued by daemons 
nevermore!
Her gentle smile spared by mine 
knightly sword!
197:
At last, long last I understood—
The will to defend is the power of 
Knighthood!
204:
As long as I've got someone to 
protect, my shield will NEVER break!
216:
That was a perfect shield bash, Miles. 
Thank you for saving me.
225:
Oh, you two are finally back. 
Did it take you a while to find the 
herbs?
229:
We were attacked by a wild boar, 
and...
234:
And Miles fended it off with his shield.
The shield shattered, though.
239:
That's all right, shields can be fixed. 
Your safety is what matters.
242:
Sounds like you had a REAL adventure. 
Welcome back.
246:
And so Miles the Knight was reunited 
with his companions, and all were 
merry!
